thread bashing that person with everyone screaming FACT FACT FACT some of them even that werent present. Even my own guild doesnt know the entire story about it they never knew what went on between me and Tristadorn they only know what itold them to do so they have basically no right perspective though i can understand they wish to defend themselves.<br>
<br>
Btw being born in Slovenia english isnt my native language so i dont even understand all the insults that are thrown at me/add so ill not lower myself to responding to them.<br>
<br>
There are people that know me well .. do well in fact that they could have put their hand in the flames for me telling the truth ... though i seriously doubt that they frequent flame boards since theyre nice people ... i would never be aware of this bashing at me had my guild not told me theres a thread here about .. so maybe with everyones allowance i may perhaps give my side of the story which has a bit more to it than Tristadorns 3 point story.<br>
<br>
I was in fact never present there since i was levling my wifes cleric but i do hold ultimate authority over what happened in PoF since add never made a move untill i allowed it or ordered it. I was the most senior officer online at that moment so it fell to me to lead negotiations when it became apparent that there were 2 guilds competing for shissar. <br>
<br>
Let me firstly answer the 3 points made by Tris about it ...<br>
1st point was Radiant was in zone 1st. Actually a druid Neomorpheous was in zone 1st for 3 hours straight before Radiant was even aware of the spawn or so i beleive ... i have no idea when they became aware of the spawn but i knew it was up for all CeT afternoon and Neo was there to keep observing till ppl logged on. If Radiant was first in zone with 1 group yes indeed they were(more explanation of ,why didnt we just stop then as we should have and would if it had happened as Tristadorn describes it, will follow). <br>
<br>
Point 2 and 3 kind of fall into same category ... who aggroed 1st and who pulled 1st .. same thing ... i would never allow pulling some mob that was already pulled except if it was kited around by someone to prevent ADDs sufficient force to engage it till his/her friends could come in (which wasnt the case here so the last part of the sentence is just explaining my way of thinking. I personally dont give a @#%$ about PnP because thats official name for something formal that everyone of us should understand in their hearts and not try to find loop holes in the technicalities of the rule). I asked in /gu and Verbo personally if they have aggroed or have engaged the mob before i gave the order to pull. After the mob was pulled i asked again very specifically if the mob was within its room on the top of temple when verbo aggroed it ... i specifically asked him if the mob was moving when he aggroed it his response was yes it was in the top room and no it was not moving. I had no reason to disbeleive Verbo at that point nor do i now.<br>
<br>
Before i even start more closely explaining my side of the story i would like to say that yes Maeve is one of the nicest people in EQ and im deeply saddened she was hurt. Though in my opinion it was purely Tristadorns fault any of this even occured. Whether he did what he did out of some malicious reason or purely by misunderstanding my orders were in direct response to Tristadorns tells and actions of Radiant that i was reported from my guild.<br>
<br>
Okay to my side of the story now. As i said before we spotted mob well prior to the raid in question but we didnt have the ppl online to do it so we said as soon as some ppl log on we go get it. It was for Qindien that the mob was intended to die.<br>
<br>
As for Tristadorns claim that his guild was in fear well before we even started to contact him is a blatant lie. Tristadorn himself was not even on the continent when have already been sending tells to various Radiant members for at least 15 minutes while they directed me from one of ficer to the other out which i could not get anything but total silence. Only one officer responded to me saying that he will be Raid leader in chief WHEN he gets there (notice that even the raid leader was nowhere near feerott wehn i already had guildies in feerot and was already trying to reason a deal). After i got the confirmation that hes the person to talk to i proceeded to try to work out some agreement. After being ignored totally for another 5 minutes while i was sending tells in the manner /tell &quot;officer i cantremember you name&quot; are you still there  and similar i finally get a response from him telling me that he isnt the person to talk to after all and that i should talk to Tristadorn ... well what else to do (some of my guildies being in feerott joking about contest between a ranger and a monk who would outdamage who on spectres there and ofcourse waiting for my order to move in ... i namely told them to stay put till i talk to Radiant) i send tell to Tristadorn who was still in echo caverns at that time i beleive again all the response i get is &quot;sec&quot; or &quot;im busy&quot; or something in that manner im not sure of exact wording since poor naive me i dont take logs of conversations because i trust ppl wont go back on their words once theyre given. I keep waiting to get a response out of Tristadorn while he goes over to feerott and Radiant goes in (yes they did zone in 1st in force indeed... i am not absolutely certain that tristadorn was with them at 1st breakin so it may be that they ran in a bit sooner but i dont mean this as in so soon that add wasnt there cause there was a person there entire afternoon CET time and im sure i would have known if they did that.) When Radiant is finally in NC or NWC im not entirely sure which (the druid was still there reporting to me whats happening.) i finally get response from Tristadorn &quot;yes lets&quot; in response to my several times repeated suggestion &quot;lets come to some agreement over Shissar&quot;. So i say what do you suggest ... jsut roloff and loser backs off? (i would like to point that Adds force of i think 15-20 ppl was sitting in front of portal in feerott  waiting for me to finally talk to Radiant to see how we could proceed). Again after that tell i got ingnored for some minutes (except telling me that i would get pettitioned and reported for training if we zone in (when again for the Xth time i tell my guild not to go in and mess wiht their cr .. told them to wait that im still talking to them) ... somwhere in that time frame that druid spotter tells me Radiant got wiped again so that might explain why Tristadorn couldnt respond though with the new caching tells im sure he didnt miss any of my tells... i didnt think of that before so i told tristadorn im beginning to feel stalled with promises of agreement. At that point he assures me that im not being stalled and the &quot;agreement talk continues&quot;. I again suggest we roll off and he says he isnt ok with that. So i say &quot;okay man make it a competition then and we say whoever clears to it 1st gets it .. best man wins fair and sqare&quot;. He says hes not okay with that and that they dont want an agreement now since they feel they deserve the mob over us since theyre already up there (all the time leading up to this statement i did not allow my guild who was there in more than sufficient force to zone in because i was talking to Trist about agreement and didnt want ppl to run in and possibly get killed when we could have possibly lost that roll that i was trying to talk about with Trist so unsucsesfully or we didnt wanna ruin their CR (i think we even offered to do their cr for it but it wasnt done by me so i wont put my hand into flame over it)). I said that i cant accept that in no way (would you expect me to have someone ignore me while i try to talk to him ... move past me while i wait for him to respond ... wait for him to get killed rezzed killed again rezzed again while all the time hes letting me beleive that well reach some agreement ... then when he is in superior position to point at PnP rules refuse to reach agreement and basically says i dont want agreement now cause im in place to pull the mob and u suckers are still waiting outside the zone *not his exact wording but thats how i understood it*) to which he responds ill petition and let GM settle it. I agree to that since thats at least SOME sort of agreement and i pettition GMs asking for assistance in a dispute over a mob ... at that time 3 Guides were online so i figure okay should be quick. (all the time my guild is nagging at me why cant they go in and i tell them to stay put till i get GM response). So i wait for that GM to respond and ppl sit around in feerott some more ... my watcher in Fear is reporting to me all the time that Radiant force is clearing way to shissar and not in any matter waiting for GMs so i sent direct tells to the 2 guides twice with 5 or 10 min timeframe between them ... on both occasions i was told to wait that theyll get to it when they have time. I ask the spotter again if he is absolutely sure Radiant is running for the shissar and he says that he honestly beleives they will not wait for GMs but simply pull. At that point i make the decision and order guild to move in clear way and pull and kill the Shissar IF Radiant didnt already engage or would pull/engage while we were runnign in/ clearing. How the pull was done i have explained earlier .. i checked before the pull and after the pull if the mob was aggroed or not. On both counts i received negative response. We killed the mob ... at this point i was still fully willing to roll for it but then my guild reported Tristadorn himself bringing a train to our force at which point i told Qindien to loot it and the hell with the training ... as it happened everyone was wiped out in that train but Qindien was still able to loot the piece. Even though it was 1 am then i kept awake for 2 hours till petition ran out if any GMs respond and when they didnt i finally logged. Today i find this thread of 70+ posts here of what all manner of objects and animals ADD is and me peronsally w/o ever hearing my side of the story. <br>
<br>
To further explain my standpoint here ... i have nothing against Radiant personally i was never present at any of the trouble add and radiant were supposed to have in the past but i can imagine with Tristadorns lack of diplomatic courtesy or tact agreements come very hard. I dont hold any grudges against  Radiant as a guild ... what they beleive happened there is probably because Tristadorn was playing this game of hide and seek and the carrot on a stick wawing in front of my face to delay add and gain himself stronger position from which he could just forget any agreement and fall back on PnP technicalities. Id also like to say that ADD as a guild had nothing to do there ... they only followed my orders and they werent fully informed of the situation as i suspect Radiant wasnt.<br>
<br>
Now to the the essence of the mile long post which i couldnt have just presented w/o ppl that had nothing at all with the matter aside from knowing Maeve or Tristadorn or me for that matter. This is a flame board which is useless for anything other than spreading rumor and dissent so ill make a shock and make a statement here that might actually be constructive in regard to the incident. Ill try to be as objective as i possibly can here. <br>
<br>
Let us return to tristadorns 3 points ... <br>
Point one ... the point is true .. Radiant was first in force in fear but only because of the stalling and letting me beleive that we would reach an agreement before any of us went in. That was done not only by Tristadorn but by other members/officers before him (just for the record Maeve was casting c3 in Fungus grove on me and my wife when add was already gathering for Shissar).<br>
<br>
Point 2 and 3 ... i checked and doublechecked we were 1st on the pull and both checks proved positive ... for the sake of argument i will allow a chance that Verbo was mistaken about it or lied to me about it(very doubtfull). I suggest we both petition and let GMs search their logs and i will personally make a formal apology if it turns out that Radiant did in fact aggro first and GM will move item to Maeve. Qindien will not be allowed to use the item to complete epic untill this is resolved.<br>
<br>
My standpoint to Tristadorn ... i thought highly of him even though not knowing him very well as a fellow paladin and a skilled player. Now though i would wish to beleive his deceiving/manipulating me was just a boatload of misunderstandings, LDs in innapropriate moments or zoning to miss tells or plain simple missing some tells in battle spam i am being hard pressed that anything like that would be possible to such an extent.<br>
<br>
Maeve i deeply apologise for any hurt my actions have caused you ... what i did was never intended to hurt you in any way but was solely reacting to Tristadorn. Even though i dont know you well and mostly from hearsay i am to understand that you are one of the nicest people one could possibly meet and i grieve when the biggest @#%$ happens to the nicest people. I understand that you feel angered and cheated but had Tristadorn been more diplomatic you might have had your epic in your hand now. Even sentences such as &quot;This would be our first ench epic in guild and its her last please please let us have the mob.&quot; have been known to sway my resolve in the past but with the lack of respect i was treated by Tristadorn i saw no other way to respond. I wont say anything about what the people in my guild would do or say cause not all are as level headed as me but personally if i can help you in any way i would do so in an instant to make up for the hurt this has caused you. I hold no grudge agaisnt anyone in Radiant for all the cursing and namecalling earlier and i apologise for any uncivil behaviour of co guildies. It was always my beleif that we are all adults and could resolve our differences or deal with conflicting interests withought mindgames and sensless flameboard bashing.<br>
<br>
